    pages = "169--173",
    abstract = "$\beta$-NMR studies of delocalization of polarization of 8Li $\beta$-active nuclei in spatially disordered 8Li--6Li nuclear system in LiF single crystals are presented. Unique peculiarity of the investigated 8Li--6Li nuclear spin system is that the g-factors of these isotopes are very close. So, the cross-relaxation between them dominates over all other depolarization mechanisms. Depolarization kinetics of 8Li nuclear probe in LiF crystals are measured in a wide range of 6Li concentration: 0.15, 3.28, 5.30, 8.81, and 10.06{\%} and retraced up to (8--10) T1/2(8Li). The obtained data show good agreement with theoretical descriptions.",
